%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% re_burr - Burr elastic image registration
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% This routine performs one iteration of the Burr
% elastic image registration method.  The algorithm
% begins by computing a feature displacement vector
% (FDV) for each pixel in both the ref and dist images.
% The size of the FDV window limits the maximum
% displacement of any given pixel.  The SAID
% correlation measure is used to determine the
% similarity between pixels.  The SAID window size
% determines the window over which the terms of this
% correlation are summed.  Finally, the 'pushing' and
% 'pulling' FDV's are combined to determine the actual
% displacement of the pixel.  Only FDV's with in the
% cooperative neighborhood window are employed in
% finding this final displacement.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
